An S4 class to represent a collection of gamma sectra

Source: R/AllClasses.R, R/extract.R
GammaSpectra.Rd

Represents a collection of spectra of gamma ray spectrometry measurements.

# S4 method for GammaSpectra
[(x, i, j)

# S4 method for GammaSpectra
[[(x, i)

Arguments

x

An object of class GammaSpectrum.
i, j

Indices specifying elements to extract or replace (see below). Indices are numeric or character vectors or empty (missing) or NULL. Numeric values are coerced to integer as by as.integer (and hence truncated towards zero). Character vectors will be matched to the names of the object.

Details

This class extends the base list and can only contains GammaSpectrum objects.

Methods

estimateBaseline

Estimate the baseline of each gamma spectrum in a GammaSpectra object. See estimateBaseline for details.

estimateDoseRate

Estimate the in-situ gamma dose rate of each gamma spectrum in a GammaSpectra object. See estimateDoseRate for details.

findPeaks

Look for local maxima to extract peaks out of each gamma spectrum in a GammaSpectra object. See findPeaks for details.

removeBaseline

Estimate and remove the baseline of each gamma spectrum in a GammaSpectra object. See removeBaseline for details.

Access

In the code snippets below, x is a GammaSpectra object.

length(x)

Get the number of elements in x.

names(x), names(x) <- value

Get or set the names of the elements according to value.

Coerce

In the code snippets below, x is a GammaSpectra object.

as(x, "list")

Coerces x to a list.

Subset

In the code snippets below, x is a GammaSpectra object.

x[i]

Extracts the elements selected by subscript i. i can be missing or NULL, numeric or character vector or a factor. Returns a new GammaSpectra object.

x[i, j]

Like the above but allows to select a slot thru j (see examples). j is a character vector of length one. Returns a list.

x[[i]]

Extracts the elements selected by subscript i. i can be a numeric or character vector of length one. Returns the corresponding GammaSpectrum object.

See also

GammaSpectrum.
